div.div:
Session State:
- Similar to Redux in React.JS
- Allow to save information for each user that is preserved between reruns.
- Session is tied to a single tab. Session resets if the user reload the URL.
- Widgets handle their statefulness all by themselves, so you won't always need to use Session State!

Widgets:
- All widget are given 'id' by default which can be modified by explicitly passing 'key' argument
- Each widget has its own session state
- When the widget is hidden/destroyed, its session state is removed

Fragments:
- Streamlit triggers a fragment rerun instead of a full rerun when they interact with that fragment's widget
- Do not return value from Fragment. Use Session State to share data across Fragments
- If you need to trigger a full-script rerun from inside a fragment, call st.rerun
